"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nGeneral\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nFrom: reno design &lt;reno@renodesign.com.au&gt;<br />\nSubject: [POSEN] Fromm family<br />\nDate: Thu, 29 Jul 2010 19:04:43 +1000\n</p>\n<p>\n&nbsp;\n</p>\n<p>\nHello\n</p>\n<p>\nI am located in Sydney, Australia and doing part-time research into my<br />\nfather\u00b9s family.<br />\nCan anyone offer advice on a \u008cFromm\u00b9 family who appear to have been located<br />\nin Poznan/Posen, possibly in Gniezno/Gnesen in the early 1800s.<br />\nI am initially interested in confirming the \u008cbirth places\u00b9, \u008cparents\u00b9 and<br />\n\u008cany siblings\u00b9 of the brothers Samuel and Victor Fromm.<br />\nThe family name may have been \u008cFromm\u00b9 or \u008cFrome\u00b9 or \u008cFrom\u00b9.<br />\nAll birth dates indicated in sections 4 and 5 below are as accurate as I<br />\nknow.\n</p>\n<p>\nBasic findings of research derived from a UK researcher, UK censuses, birth<br />\ncertificates, marriage certificates, naturalisation papers, etc, shows:\n</p>\n<p>\n1. Me: Graham Rendoth: b.1957-, Tamworth NSW Australia\n</p>\n<p>\n2. My father: Cedric Victor Rendoth: b.1932- , Sydney NSW Australia\n</p>\n<p>\n3. My grandfather: Albert Rendoth \u00ad changed his name when he migrated to<br />\nAustralia c.1911. (employ: waiter)<br />\nHis birth name is apparently Arthur Fromm*: b.1890, Mile End, London,<br />\nEngland d.1975 Sydney Australia\n</p>\n<p>\n4a. Father of Albert Rendoth (Arthur Fromm): Henry Samuel Ludwig Fromm (HSL<br />\nFromm): b.1864-1930, Kingsland, Hackney, London, England (mercantile clerk,<br />\npostman)<br />\n4b. Mother of Albert Rendoth (Arthur Fromm): Rose Matilda Fromm (nee<br />\nWilkinson): b.1867-1938, Kingsland, London, England<br />\nMarried 24 Feb 1886, Hackney, London.<br />\nChildren: Albert Edward, Henry Alfred, Claude W, *Arthur, George, Samuel,<br />\nCecilia Marion, Rose Lilian.<br />\nThere is one record that indicates that aged in their mid-teens and 20s the<br />\nchildren George, Arthur, Samuel and Cecilia may have used the surname<br />\n\u008cSmith\u00b9.\n</p>\n<p>\n5a. Father of HSL Fromm: Samuel Fromm: b.1838, Posen (city or province?)<br />\nd.1912, Southwark London (employ: restaurant manager, wine merchant,<br />\npublican)<br />\nApplied to become a Naturalised British subject in 1862.<br />\n5b. Mother of HSL Fromm and wife of Samuel Fromm: Marion Fromm (nee<br />\nMoggridge): b.1839, Dalston, Hackney, London<br />\nMarried 1861, Hackney, London. Number of children is unknown<br />\nSamuel remarried to Emily Gentry (publican) in 1904. No children.\n</p>\n<p>\n5c. Brother of Samuel Fromm: Victor Fromm: b.1832, Gnesen, Posen, Prussia<br />\n(employ: general agent, bootmaker)<br />\nArrived in England c.1860. Applied to become a Naturalised British subject<br />\nin 1873.<br />\nVictor had a daughter, Franziska b.1870. At about 3 years of age she was<br />\napparently sent to Germany \u008cfor the good of her health\u00b9.<br />\nHis wife\u00b9s name and birthpalce is not known.\n</p>\n<p>\nI am aware of the LDS Family Library Catalogue and currently deciding if I<br />\nwill order microfilm/microfisch copies to be sent to the LDS Family History<br />\nCenter closest to where I live.\n</p>\n<p>\nLook forward to any assistance and information.\n</p>\n<p>\nGraham\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
