"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nIt isn't clear to me when and how Rosina Curtis Jones fits into this picture.\n</p>\n<p>\nThe occupation of Victor Fromm in the census data is bootmaker. The same as on Henry Leopold Fromm's christening paperwork. That suggests that they are one person.\n</p>\n<p>\nHenry Leopold was born before Victor married Heneriette Behrens, and on the marriage certificate it says he was a bachelor.<br />\nSo, the relationship with Rosina Curtis Jones pre-dates that marriage, and I can't find any marriage paperwork between Rosina and Victor ... did they ever actually get married?\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nGeneral\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nAccording to Greg Smith (his nephew), \"His brother bill I. Remember and walked with a limp from a childhood accident being thrown from a horse in his early teens. I also recall meeting his sisters rush and one we called Winn, I guess she must have been the youngest one, they were lovely people as I recollect.\"\n</p>\n<p>\nI assume Rush was in fact Ruth. I'm not sure who Winnie would be, unless it was also Ruth Winifred Fromm.\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
